annotation.TEXT: Missed. Try again.
You can't reach all of these coins by jumping from the net, but a running jump from the ground on the right will get you up there!
Hello, and welcome back to another exciting (maybe) episode of Chaos CompleXX!
Okay, that's the only reason I wanted to revisit this level. Now, back to the castle!
Gotta love the pink theme this level has going on!
Oh, and there's a fancy looking midpoint, along with the keyhole, but where could the key be?
Wow, I sucked at that multi-coin block! Now, before I head back for the secret exit, I'm just going to make sure none of these turn blocks are hiding anything...
Keep stomping duders without letting your feet land on anything solid if you can, so you can build up a combo.
You can stock up on flowers here, but I'm going to keep one cape, just in case.
GIGA DRILL BR- Uh, oh...
Now, I've placed the voting results in the video description (as trying to annotate them would be kind of a hassle), but I will say here that it appears to be a tie between koopers and duders!
Up next, we have Rosa Perplex 1. Hmm... Do I have enough time for another level in this video?
Well, it's not like I needed that flower, since there's a feather up ahead anyway!
And actually, Yoshi can't exactly make this jump very easily, so jumping off a Lakitu is a handy way to get Yoshi up there!
Okay, now I'm all powered up and ready to go...
Castle goes boom!
Well, at least I had gotten all the Yoshi coins and hit midpoint...
Methinks I did not think that one through...
I'm sure some of us have accidentally failed to hit a midpoint at one time or another...
Yep, it's a trap! You can't duck under the pillars like you could here in the original SMW!
I'll just fly up here and start using some spiral power!
Okay, so I found the key, but I don't want to activate the secret exit just yet. I want to get all the Yoshi coins first!
Good thing the game made sure I hit midpoint! Otherwise, I'd have to replay the entire level! Now, I'm going to backtrack a bit for some feathers here...
Barf! Well, that midpoint power up sure lasted a long time... At least I still have my reserve flower!
Also, you can climb up this vine, but I don't think it goes anywhere special.
Iggy himself is unchanged, but you should have feathers to help you out, making the fight easier than usual (if that's even possible)!

Yeah! I stomped that duder! I guess that means a 5-life stomping combo is possible here! I'm not going to go for that myself now, but if anyone else wants to try for the 5-life stomping combo here, go right ahead! (You could even make it a video response if you want!)
You can even stand on them if you want and they won't mind!
Well, that didn't work, but I could just jump around the block like this.
Alright, another feather!
It's time for fight against enemy!
Now, this fence has some red bars going through it, but you can climb over them without issues if there's netting on both sides of it.
There's some more flowers. Honestly, you should have no excuse for running out of flowers in this level!
Climb up this vine to find five Yoshi coin halves. Now, don't be fooled into thinking they're worthless. They actually will count as a whole Yoshi coin each, so you can get a 1-up right here!
Okay, back to the pillar room. Huh, was that first floating coin there last time?

Now, when you blast off from midpoint here, don't panic! You won't automatically go crashing into this paraduder! (You'll still have to paddle to avoid letting him walk into you, but you have plenty of time to react.)
Also, more koopers to punch, since I can't stomp them.
And finally, the secret exit!
Well, if the game's gonna give me a ton of feathers here, I may as well let one pillar squash me for hahas.
Over here, we have some Lakitus jumping up and down and having a blast in their little pool. They're harmless, so don't worry about them.
Yoshi coin number seven is right here, along with more vines. One ends at a hidden coin block, and the other goes all the way into the sky, but otherwise isn't special.
Oh, be careful of this green duder jammed in the wall up here. If you try to stomp him while clinging to the net...
Nope, nothing special up there, I don't think...
And of course I block clone when I didn't intend to!
4-life combo! I think that's all the duder stomping you can do in this room.

That hidden ledge actually continues under this small body of water, so if you jump just right, you can walk on the ice blocks below, allowing you to avoid a few duders and stomp a couple of fish early!
Thanks, Lakitus! Now, to collect more Yoshi coins and stomp more koopers...
Also, for some strange reason, you can hit midpoint again, giving you a free power up if you're small! (So hit it before using any reserve item you may have.)
Oh, and these duders may look slightly oddly colored, but they're definitely yellow, as evidenced by Yoshi's dust clouds.
So, last time, I held a vote as to what those koopas/koopers should be called.
Also, be careful not to fall through that almost invisible gap to your doom like I did.
Whoa! That was risky. I could've stayed on the left there, but suddenly I changed my mind and went right. (Being indecisive could be dangerous in a place like this!)
I don't think there's anything of interest in the note block ceilings here, but if I'm wrong, let me know! There definitely are items of interest in the ? blocks, though!
Hi, Yoshi!
The castle intro appears to be unchanged, not that it needs changing.
Gulp!
Oh, hey! That red kooper was briefly in a stompable position! I'm going to see if I can stomp him!
That red duder is a bit unusual. You definitely can't stomp him (I don't think), and you can't exactly punch him through a net either. You'll need a cape spin or fireballs to take him out.
Okay, so that unlocks UnderWater Roadtrip, which I'll go on later.
Oh, come on! I was so on the other side of that gate! Stupid fireball...
Its dangereros to go alone! Take this! ...Wait, that's another game.
Demo count: 6

...you get hurt for some reason! You can still stomp him, but you have to jump off the net to do so. It's still possible to maintain your combo while doing this if you regrab the net right after stomping him.
Well, I should be able to get at least one exit, so let's-a-go!
This red kooper, on the other hand, is totally unreachable with your feet. You can certainly cape spin him, though.
Right off the bat, you get launched into the air! Put on the brakes quickly, or you'll crash into the yellow parakooper at the beginning!
And then make sure you go back here to find...
So, anyway. Dodge to the left or right of the pillars, and don't fall in that hole I fell into last time.
Also, there's another trap you gotta watch out for. The autoscrolling does not stop at the door, so don't dillydally in entering it!
But what will I find on my way to the normal exit of Rosa Perplex 1? Will it include a secret that'll make me go totally lunatic? And will I ever manage to enter the bonus game?
Now for that secret exit...
Certain koopers are on the wrong side of the fence to stomp, but you can (Falcon) punch them through the net for 100 points by using the X or Y buttons.
You can also enter this small pond from the right side if you wanted.
See, there's Yoshi coin number six already! Oh, and I gotta check every pipe!
yee-ha indeed. I'm looking forward to MUCH more better ecellent levl design that rullleeees realy.
D'oh! Stupid hidden block. Maybe if I duck jump from below...
Sneak attack! Missed, but I still scared him into jumping!
And there's the last Yoshi coin, I think, so that makes ten Yoshi coins in this level total. (If I missed any, let me know!)
You can collect these coins and stomp some koopers. Also, watch out for the fireball that pops up there.
Assuming I can keep my footing...
Ooh, this place looks neat already!
Boo-yah! However, there are still more Yoshi coins in the level, so try not to die or otherwise leave the area until I say so!
Well, I'd better go to him and See, wahts happened.
Now, to the genre savvy, beware in this area!

Over here, another trick. This looks like a gap, similar to that one in the pillar room of fight against enemy, but there's actually a ledge down there, which a kooper is more than happy to demonstrate!
I'm not planning on stayying her any longer time than I need to. Also, as youwill see, they provided us with a papillion midpoint bars here, just to make sure you can't miss hitting midpoint somehow.
So, I guess I'll just switch between those two names throughout this episode. For example, I'm using this kooper shell to clobber this row of duders!
Find out next time! To be continued...
Nuts. I forgot to duck before jumping onto the fence, so I don't think I can get that flower without breaking my combo...
Demo count: 7
